I will suddenly make him run away from her. And I will appoint over her whomever I choose. For who is like me? Who will summon me? What shepherd can stand before me? </span><span class=\"v24_49_20\"><sup id=\"Jer.49.20\" class=\"v24_49_20\">20</sup>Therefore hear the plan that the <span class=\"nd\">Lord</span> has made against Edom and the purposes that he has formed against the inhabitants of Teman: Even the little ones of the flock shall be dragged away. Surely their fold shall be appalled at their fate. </span><span class=\"v24_49_21\"><sup id=\"Jer.49.21\" class=\"v24_49_21\">21</sup>At the sound of their fall the earth shall tremble; the sound of their cry shall be heard at the Red Sea. </span><span class=\"v24_49_22\"><sup id=\"Jer.49.22\" class=\"v24_49_22\">22</sup>Behold, one shall mount up and fly swiftly like an eagle and spread his wings against Bozrah, and the heart of the warriors of Edom shall be in that day like the heart of a woman in her birth pains.\u201d</span></p>\n<h3 class=\"s1\">Judgment on Damascus</h3>\n<p class=\"p\"><span class=\"v24_49_23\"><sup id=\"Jer.49.23\" class=\"v24_49_23\">23</sup>Concerning Damascus:</span></p>\n<p class=\"b\"></p>\n<p class=\"q1\"><span class=\"v24_49_23\">\u201cHamath and Arpad are confounded,</span></p>\n<p class=\"q2\"><span class=\"v24_49_23\">for they have heard bad news;</span></p>\n<p class=\"q1\"><span class=\"v24_49_23\">they melt in fear,</span></p>\n<p class=\"q2\"><span class=\"v24_49_23\">they are troubled like the sea that cannot be quiet.</span></p>\n<p class=\"q1\"><span class=\"v24_49_24\"><sup id=\"Jer.49.24\" class=\"v24_49_24\">24</sup>Damascus has become feeble, she turned to flee,</span></p>\n<p class=\"q2\"><span class=\"v24_49_24\">and panic seized her;</span></p>\n<p class=\"q1\"><span class=\"v24_49_24\">anguish and sorrows have taken hold of her,</span></p>\n<p class=\"q2\"><span class=\"v24_49_24\">as of a woman in labor.</span></p>\n<p class=\"q1\"><span class=\"v24_49_25\"><sup i